<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-7659] cqlsh: DESCRIBE KEYSPACE should order types according to cross-type dependencies</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7659</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Since UDTs may use other UDTs for fields, DESCRIBE KEYSPACE should list types in an order that handles the dependencies.  This was recently done in the python driver here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/datastax/python-driver/pull/165&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/datastax/python-driver/pull/165&lt;/a&gt;.  We can either update to the latest python driver, or copy that code for cqlsh.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12731117">CASSANDRA-7659</key>
            <summary>cqlsh: DESCRIBE KEYSPACE should order types according to cross-type dependencies</summary>
