                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14083196" author="iamaleksey" created="Fri, 1 Aug 2014 23:40:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;With &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7656&quot; title=&quot;UDT with null/missing attributes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-7656&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-7656&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in, this should now be resolved as well?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14086498" author="thobbs" created="Tue, 5 Aug 2014 17:16:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No, cqlsh puts together the user types for the &lt;tt&gt;DESCRIBE KEYSPACE&lt;/tt&gt; output itself, so just upgrading the python driver wasn&apos;t enough.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14087159" author="mishail" created="Wed, 6 Aug 2014 02:40:18 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;No, cqlsh puts together the user types for the DESCRIBE KEYSPACE output itself&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That was done only because driver didn&apos;t support UDTs at that time. Now we have to switch to driver&apos;s functionality.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14098145" author="mishail" created="Fri, 15 Aug 2014 04:52:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I would extend the scope of this ticket to &quot;remove &lt;tt&gt;pylib.cqlshlib.cql3handling.UserTypesMeta&lt;/tt&gt; in favor of &lt;tt&gt;cassandra.metadata.UserType&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;, that would cover the original issue as well&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14098726" author="thobbs" created="Fri, 15 Aug 2014 16:26:09 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;I would extend the scope of this ticket to &quot;remove pylib.cqlshlib.cql3handling.UserTypesMeta in favor of cassandra.metadata.UserType&quot;, that would cover the original issue as well&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14104120" author="thobbs" created="Wed, 20 Aug 2014 16:55:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;7659-2.1.txt uses the python driver to describe UDTs.  I also did some minor cleanup in cql3handling.py to make my linter happy &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14104407" author="thobbs" created="Wed, 20 Aug 2014 19:31:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The v2 patch fixes some field name and layout fetching for autocompletion that I missed in the v1 patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14105588" author="iamaleksey" created="Thu, 21 Aug 2014 16:59:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LGTM, +1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14105795" author="thobbs" created="Thu, 21 Aug 2014 19:01:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
